<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/logo' %>
<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/date', :locals => {notice: notice} %>
<%= render partial: "notices/shared/address", :locals => {notice: notice} %>

<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><h3>Denial of Application to Renew Group Health Coverage in DC Health Link</h3></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<table class="total_table" border="0">
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Dear <%= notice.employer_name %>:  </td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "Thank you for applying to renew your group health coverage through #{Settings.site.short_name}. However, based upon the information you have provided in your account, your group does not meet #{Settings.site.short_name} eligibility criteria #{notice.primary_address} as listed below. This means that the health insurance contract(s) between you, #{notice.employer_name}, and the health insurance carrier(s) will be terminated effective #{notice.plan_year.end_on} and your group will not renew coverage through DC Health Link on <Renewal Effective Date>"} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
 content: "You may appeal through any of the following methods:"} %>
  <table class="total_table" border="0">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>
          <ul>
            <li style="margin-top: 0px;">
              Employers continue to meet residency requirements:
              <ul>
                <li>Have your principal business address in the District of Columbia and offer coverage to all full-time employees through <%= Settings.site.short_name %>, OR</li>
                <li>Continue to offer coverage through <%= Settings.site.short_name %> to all full-time employees whose primary worksite is located in the District of Columbia and offer coverage to non-DC based employees through the SHOP exchange serving their primary worksite(s); </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              At least two-thirds of your eligible employees need to enroll in your group health coverage or waive due to having other coverage; and
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
              One non-owner employee enrolls in health coverage.
          </li>
          </ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "For more information about SHOP employer eligibility requirements, please see 45 C.F.R. 155.710"} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
  content: "Please note that you can reapply for employer-sponsored coverage with #{Settings.site.short_name} at any time."} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => {
  contents: [""],
    heading: 'For Questions or Assistance:', sub_heading: ''} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', locals: {
 content: "You can contact #{Settings.site.short_name} with any questions:"} %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/unordered_list', :locals => { listings:
                                                                 ["By calling #{notice.hbe.phone}.",
                                                                  "TTY: 711",
                                                                  "Online at <a href='www.DCHealthLink.com'>www.DCHealthLink.com</a>"]} %>

<% if notice.broker.present? %>
  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/broker_contact_info', :locals => {broker: notice.broker} %>
<% else %>
  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
 content: "If you do not currently have a broker, you can reach out to one of our many trained experts by clicking on the “Find a Broker” link in your employer account or calling #{Settings.contact_center.phone_number}."} %>
<% end %>

<%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
 content: "This notice is being provided in accordance with 45 C.F.R 155.715(e)."} %>

<div class="page_break">

  <td align="center"><h2 style="text-decoration:underline;"><%= Settings.site.short_name %> SHOP Employer Appeal Rights</h2></td>
  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "If you do not agree with our decision about whether or not you are an eligible employer, you have a right to appeal our decision and receive a Fair Hearing.  Employers have the right to appeal a denial of eligibility, the failure of DC Health Benefit Exchange (HBX) to provide a timely eligibility determination, or the failure of the DC HBX to provide a timely notice of an eligibility determination."} %>

  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "You have 90 days from the date of the eligibility notice to request an appeal.  If you do not appeal within 90 days, you may lose your appeal right"} %>


  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => {
    contents: [""],
      heading: 'How to Request an Appeal', sub_heading: ''} %>
  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "You may appeal through any of the following methods:"} %>
    <table class="total_table" border="0">
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>
            <ul>
              <li style="margin-top: 0px;">
                Calling <%= Settings.site.short_name %> Customer Service toll free at 1-855-532-5465
                <ul>
                  <li>Can be mailed, faxed, or e-mailed</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
                Completing a SHOP Request for Hearing Form, available at DCHealthLink.com/Forms
              </li>
              <li style="margin-top: 5px;">
                Going to the Office of Administrative Hearings Resource Center, located at 441 4th Street, NW, Suite 450-North, Washington, DC 20001, where you can fill out a Request for Hearing form.
            </li>
            </ul>
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => {
    contents: [""],
      heading: 'What Happens When You Appeal', sub_heading: ''} %>

  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "Once your appeal is received, it simultaneously triggers both an informal and formal review process."} %>

  <table class="total_table" border="0">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><h3><b><i>Informal Review</i></b> – You may be contacted by a staff member within HBX to review your eligibility and enrollment history with the intent of exploring whether your appeal can be resolved short of a formal hearing.  Engaging in this informal review is optional both for you and for HBX</h3></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><h3><b><i>Formal Review</i></b> – You will be scheduled for a Fair Hearing before an Administrative Law Judge.  The Fair Hearing will take place at the DC Office of Administrative Hearings (OAH) at 441 4th Street, NW, Suite 450-North, Washington, DC 20001. OAH will contact you and tell you when and where your Fair Hearing will take place. OAH will send you a scheduling order, including the time and date of your Fair Hearing.</h3></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "At the Fair Hearing, you can testify, have others testify for you, and submit documents.  At the hearing, HBX representatives will also ask questions of you and other people who testify. HBX representatives will also be permitted to present witnesses and documents. You will be able to ask questions of the HBX witnesses.  After completion of the Fair Hearing, the Administrative Law Judge will make a decision in writing and sent it to you and HBX.  The decision will also tell you what you can do if you do not agree with the decision."} %>

  <table class="total_table" border="0">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><h3>Any decisions by OAH about your employer’s eligibility for benefits might also change the eligibility of your employees and their dependents.</h3></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph_with_headers', :locals => {
    contents: [""],
      heading: 'Ending your Appeal Early', sub_heading: ''} %>


  <%= render partial: 'notices/shared/paragraph', :locals => {
   content: "You may withdraw your request for a Fair Hearing at any time before the Administrative Law Judge makes a final written decision. This includes before the hearing, potentially as a result of your informal resolution with HBX. To withdraw your request for a Fair Hearing, you must  send a written withdrawal request, including your name and case number, to the Office of Administrative Hearings by e-mail (oah.filing@dc.gov) or regular mail (441 4th Street NW, Suite 450-North). Please also send a copy of this request to HBX at SHOP.Appeals@dc.gov."} %><br>

  <table class="total_table" border="0">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>If you withdraw your request for a Fair Hearing because HBX has promised to change its decision, we will implement the new HBX decision.<b>If you stop your appeal before the agency has changed its decision, the eligibility determination will be implemented as it is written in the notice you first received before you filed your appeal.</b></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
